    Barangay Cogorin Ibaba

    Lopez, Quezon

    Announcements

    Mission

    Bigyan ng panahon at tuparin sa sinumpaang tungkulin ng walang pag aalinlang at patuloy na labanan ang kahirapan maiparatig sa mga mamamayan ang tapat na paglilingkod at pagsikapang maiangat ang antas ng edukasyon upang magkaroon ng mga mamamayang nagkakaisa at nagtutulungan tungo sa kaunlaran.

    Vision

    Isang barangay na may masaganang panatag at maginhawa na pamumuhay na may mga mamamayang makatao, maka-diyos, makabansa, at makakalikasan na pinamumunuan ng naaasahan, matino, at mahusay na mga lider ng barangay.

    Cogorin Ibaba Muncipality of Lopez, Quezon

    Cogorin Ibaba is a barangay in the municipality of Lopez, in the province of Quezon. Its population as determined by the 2020 Census was 787. This represented 0.83% of the total population of Lopez.

    Ma. Fatima C. Vasquez

    Brgy. Chairperson

    Brgy. Chairperson's Message

    Welcome to the Barangay Cogorin Ibaba official website!

    The purpose of this website is to present information about our barangay. As the barangay chairperson of this environmentally friendly and culturally diverse barangay, it is my goal to increase public awareness of our barangay by disseminating relevant information and its vision and objectives.

    It is my hope that as you peruse our webpage, news feed, and many more, you will be able to get the information you need to actively participate in the operations of Barangay Cogorin Ibaba. This is for the benefit of my dear people.

    Location & Geography

    Cogorin Ibaba is situated at approximately 13.8251, 122.2887, in the island of Luzon. Elevation at these coordinates is estimated at 87.0 meters or 285.4 feet above mean sea level.

    About Lopez

    the Municipality of Lopez (Tagalog: Bayan ng Lopez), is a 1st class municipality in the province of Quezon, Philippines. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 94,657 people
